f=Executive Office/vista/operational/skill/vista-skill-routing.md · p=Vista's routing map: which skill hands off which, what depends what. Sourced Boundaries/Integration sections already written four skill files. request-level trigger precedence (which phrase routes where), see `operational/commands/vista-commands.md` file covers dependency relationships, phrase matching. · h2:Where Identity Fits=Vista identity identity content department-leader-only (marcus holds Executive Office's), vista's principles Universal-only. tone layer sits top routing map. · h2:The Quarterly Cycle=`north-star-metric          (defines the NSM, input metrics, guardrails — \· \|                     the goal everything else calibrates against) \· v \· rice-prioritization        (sequences the backlog into a committed roadmap, \· \|                     Impact calibrated against the NSM goal)` · h2:The Quarterly Cycle=Vista's four skills form loop runs once quarter: · h2:Handoff Rules=**north-star-metric rice-prioritization**: rice's Stage calibration needs one goal Impact; goal NSM (or one input metrics). NSM exists yet, run north-star-metric first rather calibrating rice against hoc goal., **rice-prioritization roadmap-sync**: roadmap-sync runs against *committed* roadmap. none exists, Phase fallback routes back rice-prioritization., **roadmap-sync marcus**: flagged item's cut/defer/accelerate decision escalates marcus. Vista recommends; marcus decides. decision reshuffles remaining capacity trigger rice re-run., **north-star-metric roadmap-sync**: NSM inputs tiebreaker cut-vs-accelerate recommendations ("feeds top NSM input accelerate before cutting")., **okr-quality-checker marcus/okr-cascade**: marcus's okr-cascade *creates* OKRs; vista's okr-quality-checker *verifies grades* them. Vista never redrafts objectives quality failures route back marcus findings, rewrites., **okr-quality-checker next quarter**: end-of-quarter grades (and what drove them) input next rice calibration marcus's next cascade. · h2:Cross-Agent Boundaries=**vista/rice-prioritization marcus/venture-priority-matrix**: different altitude. Marcus ranks *ventures/initiatives* competing resource pool (6-factor weighted score); vista sequences *roadmap items/features* within venture (RICE). conflict between ventures goes marcus; conflict between features stays vista., **vista touch echo's territory**: metrics vista defines (NSM, guardrails) appear echo's investor updates, echo owns communication vista owns definition stay factually consistent. · h2:Precedence Request Matches Multiple Skills=See `operational/commands/vista-commands.md` specific precedence rules (score-what disambiguation, sequencing-vs-monitoring). anything covered there, route whichever skill matches request's specific, primary ask. · f=request doesn't fit anywhere map, ask what's actually asked rather forcing nearest skill consistent skill's clarify-first guidance.